text.section:
The General Assembly recognizes that the Center:
Shall serve as the central repository for materials, data, and information related to violence prevention programs operating in the State or available to the State;
May serve as a referral source for violence prevention programs and services operating in the State or available to the State;
May implement volunteer prevention networks throughout the State;
May provide research and evaluation services in the area of violence prevention;
May provide information services regarding violence prevention programs and services;
May provide or facilitate violence prevention education and training programs;
May provide media and media-related services in the area of violence prevention; and
May provide educational and academic support to disruptive youth.
